    <text>
        <body>
            <head>192. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                    (<persName corresp="rectQC2yY4UhXLeKu">Brzezinski</persName>) to President
                    <persName corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8">Carter</persName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d192fn1">Source: Carter Library,
                    National Security Affairs, Brzezinski Material, Brzezinski Office File, Country
                    Chron File, Box 50, Tunisia. Confidential. Highland initialed for <persName
                        corresp="rectQC2yY4UhXLeKu">Brzezinski</persName>. <persName
                        corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8">Carter</persName> initialed the
                    memorandum.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1977-08-11"
                        >August 11, 1977</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <list type="subject">
                <head>SUBJECT</head>
                <item>Waiver of $40 Million Ceiling on <gloss target="#t_FY_1">FY</gloss> 1977 <rs
                        type="topic" corresp="recoKawZ2IOcE8nyB">Military Assistance</rs>, Credits
                    and Guaranties for African Countries Under Section 3(b) of the <rs
                        type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recf7oWPDGyUlNNf7">Arms Export Control
                        Act</rs>, as Amended.</item>
            </list>
            <p>I attach at Tab B<note n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d192fn2">Tabs A–D are not attached.
                    Tab B is printed as <ref target="#d190">Document 190</ref>.</note> a memorandum
                from the Secretary of State recommending a Presidential Determination (at Tab A) to
                waive the $40 million statutory ceiling on the total (excluding training) of grant
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recoKawZ2IOcE8nyB">military assistance</rs> and <rs
                    type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">foreign military sales</rs> (<gloss
                    target="#t_FMS_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">FMS</rs>
                </gloss>) credits and guaranteed loans to African countries in <gloss
                    target="#t_FY_1">FY</gloss> 1977. This waiver will permit implementation of
                    <gloss target="#t_FMS_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">FMS</rs>
                </gloss> financing programs, especially progress payments on prior purchases. The
                Act permits you to waive the ceiling when you determine that a waiver is important
                to <gloss target="#t_US_1">US</gloss> security, and promptly so report to the
                    <orgName corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">Congress</orgName>.</p>
            <p>The $40 million ceiling has ceased to be a realistic limitation and has been waived
                successively in recent years. There is strong indication that <orgName
                    corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">Congress</orgName> assumes that the ceiling will
                again be waived. Our planned <gloss target="#t_FMS_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">FMS</rs>
                </gloss> financing in <placeName corresp="rech4Y08vWrfyBSYC">Africa</placeName> for
                    <gloss target="#t_FY_1">FY</gloss> 77 totals about $108.5 million.</p>
            <p>Your waiver of this ceiling will not conflict with our policy of restraining
                conventional <rs type="topic" corresp="rec9ptkWICFUk7Mvu">arms transfers</rs>. The
                Secretary of State will report your Determination of Waiver to <orgName
                    corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">Congress</orgName> on your behalf and provide
                    <orgName corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">Congress</orgName> with the Justification
                at Tab C.</p>
            <p>At Tab D lies <gloss target="#t_OMB_1">
                    <orgName corresp="rec0LJhvaDXM7fvRo">OMB</orgName>
                </gloss>’s memorandum concurring in the Determination of Waiver.<note n="3"
                    place="foot" xml:id="d192fn3">Printed as <ref target="#d191">Document
                    191</ref>.</note> It also points out that your making this determination would
                constitute approval of an increase in <gloss target="#t_FY_1">FY</gloss> 77 <gloss
                    target="#t_FMS_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">FMS</rs>
                </gloss> financing in <placeName corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisia</placeName>
                from $15 to $25 million. Neither I nor <gloss target="#t_OMB_1">
                    <orgName corresp="rec0LJhvaDXM7fvRo">OMB</orgName>
                </gloss> find any difficulty with such an increase. Further, <gloss
                    target="#t_OMB_1">
                    <orgName corresp="rec0LJhvaDXM7fvRo">OMB</orgName>
                </gloss> points out, and I concur, that this increase is unlikely to raise questions
                on the overall <rs type="topic" corresp="rec9ptkWICFUk7Mvu">arms transfers</rs>
                policy, since the 1978 <gloss target="#t_FMS_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">FMS</rs>
                </gloss> credit program includes $25 million for <placeName
                    corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisia</placeName>. Accordingly, if you agree, your
                approval of this increase will be transmitted to <orgName
                    corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">State</orgName> upon your signing the
                Determination.</p>
            <pb facs="0480" n="459" xml:id="pg_459"/>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">RECOMMENDATION</p>
            <p>That you sign the Presidential Determination at Tab A waiving the $40 million ceiling
                on <gloss target="#t_FY_1">FY</gloss> 77 <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="recoKawZ2IOcE8nyB">military assistance</rs> to <placeName
                    corresp="rech4Y08vWrfyBSYC">Africa</placeName>, as set out above, and approve
                the additional $10 million for <placeName corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj"
                    >Tunisia</placeName> at Tab D.<note n="4" place="foot" xml:id="d192fn4">Beneath
                    the recommendation, <persName corresp="recGhsidh5DfptJMV">Dodson</persName>
                    wrote: “signed Tab A 8/12/77, approved Tab D 8/12/77.” Presidential
                    Determination No. 77–19 and the justification, August 12, are in the Carter
                    Library, National Security Affairs, Brzezinski Material, Brzezinski Office File,
                    Country Chron File, Box 50, Tunisia.</note>
            </p>
